<br>
I've played a variety of characters.  I had a 54 druid for a while (cept she got deleted by someone hehe) and I've played a lot of other classes as well (56 cleric, 53 wizard, 56 bard, some friend's enchanters, mages, warriors,etc).  Every class seems to have it's positives and negatives.  For a long time Wizards were just terrible.  I had my wizard level 50 for months before Kunark came out and when it did, I was tired of him and he was just totally useless and not wanted in any group.  Then I started a cleric and saw the differences. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Wizards were in dire need of fixing and VI has actually made some steps in making them better.  I actually believe that VI wants the masses to be happy, but with the way each change affects the game, it's hard for them to decide what to do.  They're fairly slow about actually fixing anything (and with the new L3gend$ server, they'll take longer) but it seems like they're attempting to progress.<br>
<br>
If they would just fix pet pathing, I think most of the problems with Mage class balance would be resolved.  It would be nice to have a pet that will follow you around obediently (maybe they'll fix familiar pathing as well, so my familiar isn't on the complete opposite side of the zone).<br>
<br>
Until they fix pathing, they should just change these spells a bit so that people don't fly off of the handle when they see them.  Add a few points to the mage nuke to make it do more damage than the druid nuke and even out the DS damage and I think it would cause less arguments.<br>
<br>
