<br>
If melees/casters were balanced before the uber item drops, and they aren't afterwards, fixing casters by upgrading them automatically via 50pp vendor spells would create imbalance in the casters favor before the high level items.<br>
<br>
There is a big difference between a 60 warrior with NToV weapons and armor proccing primal weapons and a level 60 warrior with some indicolite and a couple pieces of cobalt.  Likewise there should be a difference between an average 60 mage with two or three of his 60 spells and a level 60 mage with epic, boots of bladecalling, and ancient burnout. <p><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE><center><b>Goladus Mistrydia</b></font><br>
