<br>
Necros AND Druids are the LEAST group friendly classes?<br>
<br>
I dont know about Necros, never played one.  And I am not really concerned with the druids getting an upgrade.  Verant does as verant will.   I have a druid, and that statement about choked me to death.<br>
<br>
Never seen a druid have trouble getting a group.  Ever.  Bringing heals, ports, cures, buffs, DoTs, snares/roots, etc, makes for a very group friendly class.  Notice, I didnt even say nukes, cause in my opinion, your mana should be used in other ways.  Never had a probelm soloing either, even when it was just using the Root/DoT method.<br>
<br>
Can someone else do the things above better?  Yep, I suppose so.  But not any one class.  So what if you have an enchanter to do buffs and such, an enchanter would be hard pressed to heal as well as you.  A shaman can do most of the above, but not the ports and evacs.  And with the group exp, no point in NOT having 2 or 3 healers for the tanks.<br>
<br>
